<br>
Seriously if taunt put you at the highest hate+1 when it works is it too damn hard to figure out someone who is constantly generating more aggro than the taunter will effectively negate the effects of taunt?<br>
<br>
<br>
Lets say for the hell of it: you generate the same amount of hate via melee dps as a warrior, then you cast a dot, you are ahead of them on the hate list. If you are still meleeing and so is the warrior that amount of aggro generation negates each other because they are the same, however the dot puts you ahead of the warrior in terms of aggro generation and thusly you have more hat and will have more hate than the warrior does.<br>
<br>
Now with taunt the warrior can catch up to how much hate you have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> at the time of the taunt</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. afterwards if you are still gaining more aggro than they do you will be on top of the hate list once more.<br>
<br>
