Yes, I've noticed taunt seems to have a harder time succedding vrs a huge hate gap, but it can work. I think the success of taunt is modified by how far ahead of you the top person is.<br>
<br>
Sitting, Level, and Distance all have effects on hate list. Some of these efffects seem viarable.<br>
<br>
Speaking of Viarable- If you have problems with taunt in PoP, I HIGHLY HIGHLY suggest using 2hand. I have serveral 1handers and epic, ToD, and SoG. Any of my 2handers (Cept when ToD chain procs) I can use as off tank in old world, etc. I can't pull aggro off a Dual Wielding epic war with 2hand epic, for example, in fear, no constantly. However, in PoValor, I've used 2hand epic almost exclusively, and kept aggro fairly well, from 61 to almost 65 (to 65, even, if I can get agroup while writing this.<br>
<br>
It just seems to me that 2handers taunt much better in PoP, or specically, in poV over Fear and Chardok.<br>
<br>
