<br>
My experience is that aggro varies by mob, and the variance seems somewhat level-dependant.  As an example .. in Maiden's Eye, pulling gorangas.  I can pull gatherers with the warrior all day long, slow immediately and send in the pet at the same time, and the shammy will never, ever, get aggro (unless he adds a dot or sits).  If I try the same thing on a goranga hunter, though, it makes a beeline for the shammy.  Even if I wait a couple of ticks before slowing.<br>
<br>
Similar experience pulling in UP to the zone line.  I told the group I was with, do NOT go after the mob when the warrior brings it into camp.  Wait by the bear.  And, every single time, the first cast of slow immediately turns the mob's attention to the shammy.  <br>
<br>
The same type of mob-by-mob difference seems to be true in PoN.  I don't have the same breadth of observation or the same consistency of experience, but it seems that the shammy sometimes gets aggro from treants when he slows, usually gets aggro from spiders, and almost always gets aggro from blood ravens.  <br>
<br>
I don't know if it is specific to the mobs, or if it's level-dependant.  My guess is that it has something to do with the variance between the level of the caster and the level of the mob.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quirtevans>QuirtEvans</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 8:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3015.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   One More Thought</span><hr size=1> One more thing I should have mentioned.  I've also done the zone in at UP with a level 60 shammy slowing.  The level 60 shammy also bought aggro, every single time he slowed.  Either the mob went to find him, or it summoned him, but it happened every single time.  So it may be that the AI of those mobs, either because of level or because of the zone, is such that they are attuned to aggroing slowers.  As I have said, the same is not true of all mobs in other zones.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=evyn@thesteelwarrior>Evyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/03 11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3015.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hate Decay....</span><hr size=1> was reading on this discussion about taunt, great thread.<br>
